## Architecture Overview

### DDD Adapted to Nuxt Server

Nuxt 4 is a fullstack framework — there is no separate `backend/` folder. All server-side logic lives under `server/`. DDD principles still apply, mapped to Nuxt conventions:

| DDD Concept | Nuxt location |
|---|---|
| Presentation (HTTP in/out) | `server/api/` — H3 event handlers |
| Application (business orchestration) | `server/services/` |
| Domain (entities, interfaces) | `server/domain/` |
| Infrastructure (DB, external) | `server/infrastructure/` |

### Layered Architecture

**Presentation Layer** (`server/api/`)
- H3 event handlers — thin layer, no business logic
- Parse request → call service → return response
- Handle HTTP errors with `createError()`

**Application Layer** (`server/services/`)
- Business logic and use-case orchestration
- Calls domain repositories (interfaces, not Prisma directly)
- Throws domain errors; never imports H3 or Prisma

**Domain Layer** (`server/domain/`)
- Entities: plain TypeScript classes with business rules
- Repository interfaces: contracts the infrastructure must satisfy
- Zero external dependencies

**Infrastructure Layer** (`server/infrastructure/`)
- Prisma repository implementations
- Satisfies domain repository interfaces
- Only layer that imports `@prisma/client`

### Project Structure

```
server/
├── api/                          # Presentation: H3 route handlers
│   ├── users/
│   │   ├── index.get.ts          # GET /api/users
│   │   ├── index.post.ts         # POST /api/users
│   │   └── [id].put.ts           # PUT /api/users/:id
│   └── health.get.ts             # GET /api/health
│
├── services/                     # Application: business logic
│   └── userService.ts
│
├── domain/                       # Domain: entities + interfaces
│   ├── entities/
│   │   └── User.ts
│   └── repositories/
│       └── IUserRepository.ts
│
├── infrastructure/               # Infrastructure: Prisma implementations
│   └── repositories/
│       └── PrismaUserRepository.ts
│
├── middleware/                   # Server middleware (auth, logging)
│   └── auth.ts
│
├── utils/                        # Shared server utilities
│   └── prisma.ts                 # Prisma client singleton
│
└── db/
    └── prisma/
        ├── schema.prisma         # Database schema
        ├── migrations/           # Migration history
        └── seed.ts               # Seed data
```

