## API Route Standards

### H3 Event Handlers

H3 replaces Express controllers. Each file in `server/api/` exports a default event handler.

```typescript
// server/api/users/index.get.ts
import { defineEventHandler, getQuery } from 'h3'
import { getUserService } from '~/server/services/userService'

export default defineEventHandler(async (event) => {
  const query = getQuery(event)
  const users = await getUserService().findAll({ page: Number(query.page) || 1 })
  return users
})
```

### Route File Naming

Nuxt maps file names to HTTP methods automatically:

| File | Route |
|---|---|
| `server/api/users/index.get.ts` | `GET /api/users` |
| `server/api/users/index.post.ts` | `POST /api/users` |
| `server/api/users/[id].get.ts` | `GET /api/users/:id` |
| `server/api/users/[id].put.ts` | `PUT /api/users/:id` |
| `server/api/users/[id].delete.ts` | `DELETE /api/users/:id` |

### Request Parsing

```typescript
import { defineEventHandler, readBody, getRouterParam, createError } from 'h3'
import { parse, ValiError } from 'valibot'
import { CreateUserSchema } from '~/server/domain/schemas/userSchemas'

export default defineEventHandler(async (event) => {
  const id = getRouterParam(event, 'id')
  const body = await readBody(event)

  // Validate with Valibot before reaching service
  try {
    const validatedBody = parse(CreateUserSchema, body)
    const user = await getUserService().create(validatedBody)
    return { data: user }
  } catch (error) {
    if (error instanceof ValiError) {
      throw createError({ statusCode: 422, message: 'Validation failed', data: error.issues })
    }
    throw error
  }
})
```

### Response Format

All API responses follow a consistent envelope:

```typescript
// Success — single resource
{ data: { id: 1, name: 'John' } }

// Success — collection
{ data: [...], meta: { total: 42, page: 1, limit: 10 } }

// Error (handled by createError)
{ statusCode: 404, statusMessage: 'User not found' }
```

### Error Handling

```typescript
import { createError } from 'h3'

// 404 Not found
throw createError({ statusCode: 404, statusMessage: 'User not found' })

// 422 Validation error
throw createError({ statusCode: 422, statusMessage: 'Validation failed', data: issues })

// 409 Conflict
throw createError({ statusCode: 409, statusMessage: 'Email already registered' })

// 500 is the default for unhandled errors — never expose internal details
```

